About 61 per cent of the women interviewed had at least one child, compared - 
 about 77 per cent found in the Demographic and Health Survey (DHS) (Ghana 1989).  The mean number of children ever born per women was 2.3, a little lower than what was obtained in the DHS (3.2).  Mean number of children ever born was higher in the rural (
